CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, June 12, 1965, pg. 15, reads: "KEY PARTICIPANTS AT CENTRAL WOMEN'S DAY - The success of the recent Women's Day observance at Central Baptist Church was keyed by the Rev. Sandy Ray (left), pastor of Cornerstone Baptist Church, Brooklyn, N. Y., shown exchanging ideas with the host pastor, the Rev. Isaac Green... A full day of activity included the afternoon service, which presented Mrs. W. D. Petett as speaker. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Rev. Sandy Ray (from Brooklyn), and Rev. Isaac Green, seated in Central Baptist Church, for Women's Day
